data.description: Nestled within the Davenport gated community of Tuscan Hills, this 4 bedroom, 3 bathroom home is ready to welcome a new family! Whether looking for a new home, vacation home, or investment property, this home has something to offer everyone. Mature landscaping, paver driveway, tile roof, and two-car garage greet you upon approach. Walk through the front door into a light, bright, and airy home with tons of natural lighting streaming through the large windows and neutral paint and flooring that make it truly move-in ready. A large great room made up of the living and dining areas and kitchen provides the perfect space for entertaining and family gatherings. Sliding doors in this great room open to the large patio, allowing for seamless indoor/outdoor living. Beautiful laminate flooring can be found throughout the great room and vaulted ceilings make the room feel even larger than it is. The kitchen boasts white cabinetry, granite countertops, newer appliances, closet pantry, and breakfast bar that overlooks a dinette. The home has split bedrooms with the master suite and a secondary bedroom and bathroom off the great room and two secondary bedrooms and bathroom off the front of the home. The master suite is spacious and offers patio access, laminate flooring, vaulted ceiling, large shower, and en-suite bathroom, complete with oversized, double-sink vanity, large shower, and garden tub. The adjacent secondary bedroom also offers laminate flooring and en-suite bathroom, which boasts a single-sink vanity and shower/tub combo. Both secondary bedrooms at the front of the home are good size with large windows and closets, one with carpet and one with laminate flooring. The shared bathroom has a single-sink vanity and shower/tub combo with pocket door separating the two. Out back, a huge pool deck makes the perfect space for family bbq and pool parties. A large, covered area is located against the home and that opens into an uncovered pool area, all of which is under screen enclosure. The solar heated pool and spa are great for enjoying the Florida summers and large hedges surrounding the screen enclosure provide great privacy from the neighboring homes. The home has solar panels that make the utility bill only $35-$45/month and a gas water heater and dryer result in only about a $30 bill/month! Don't miss out on your chance to call this great home your own!
